metadata.name: Aura
metadata.description:
This collection is developing aim,To record the new function of ancient sacral and emphasis on conceptual narration and contexts of people from various generations that leads to an albeit brief unconscious tranquility and isolation for passers, it also represents dailiness and monotony of people regarding to that historic and architectural texture by photographical techniques and express the form interpretation of both objective and 
subjective perceptions .

"Aura" it means, the distinctive atmosphere or quality that seems to surround and be generated by a person, thing, or place.
"the ceremony retains an aura of mystery"
